---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
  "name": "Obsidian Print",
  "url": "https://github.com/marijnbent/obsidian-print",
  "description": "Obsidian plugin that adds a print option. Print notes directly without exporting to PDF first.",
  "applicationCategory": "ProductivityApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Windows, macOS, Linux",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Marijn Bent",
    "url": "https://marijnbent.nl"
  },
  "offers": {
    "@type": "Offer",
    "price": "0",
    "priceCurrency": "EUR"
  }
};
---

<Layout
  title="Obsidian Print â€“ Marijn Bent"
  description="Obsidian plugin that adds a print option. Print notes directly without exporting to PDF first."
  schema={schema}
>
  <article class="prose-content">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Obsidian Print</h1>

    <div class="space-y-4 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Obsidian doesn't have a built-in way to print notes. You have to export to PDF first and then print that separately. It's a small thing but it gets old fast when you do it regularly.
      </p>

      <p>
        This plugin adds a print option directly in Obsidian. Select a note, hit print, done. No export step in between. It respects your note's formatting and works with most themes.
      </p>

      <p>
        Install it from the Obsidian community plugin store. Source is on <a href="https://github.com/marijnbent/obsidian-print" class="text-foreground font-medium underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground/80 transition-colors">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
